"To every man whom God has given wealth and possessions, he has also given him the ability
to eat from them, to receive his reward, and to find enjoyment in his toil; these things are the gift of God." Ecclesiastes 5:19

Anyone else ever feel disconnected from life? Like you were just going through the motions?

Many years of my life I spent in this space. Working so hard to achieve all the worldly things when in reality God was calling me back to the land.

I've had an incredible life. & I've done some kick ass things, but nothing- nothing- brings me the joy & fulfillment of working the land with my wife @hyavaldez & my stepsons & teaching others to do the same. 

Everyone is empowered when we see the fruits of our labor. Most men just don't know where to start. 

For me, it was mentorship & community. I had the skills, I just spent my whole life suppressing anything "blue collar." The reality is, we were meant to be at one with nature.

God created the systems, we are supposed to steward them. 

@selbygardens is the perfect example of this. A real life Garden of Eden. A century ago Marie Selby had a vision of paradise now hundreds of thousands have been inspired to create their own slice of heaven. (Never forget the legacy of the men & women that cultivate that dream all these years with their hands.)

Jackfruit, starfruit, & bananas are delicious & abundant. The best part is, if you set them in a permaculture ecosystem you can forget them until it's time to harvest.

To harvest:
Starfruit: less than a year (produce year round)
Bananas: 10-18 months (reseed themselves)
Jackfruit: 7 years from seed (easy to grow!) or buy local

Grow any of these on your land or on a balcony!

If you're a family man, want to reclaim your purpose through biblical masculinity & getting back to the land but don't know where to start DM me "Rise Up."

I'm taking on a few new clients who want to cultivate the man God created them to be.

What are you growing?

_______

"For God gave us a spirit not of fear but of power and love and self-control." 2TIM 1:7

God calls us to live fearlessly in all we do.

Why? Fear is man's greatest enemy.

It cause us to doubt.
It causes us to conform.
It causes us to be "nice."
It causes us to be content.
It causes us to give up faith.
It causes us to leave Gods systems.
It causes us to suppress HIS calling.

Few things in this world have helped me overcome fear like Scuba diving. 

Before my wife @hyavaldez & I got married in 2021 it was one of her requirements of a husband. 😂

Don't ask me twice- however what I looked like on the surface was far drastic to the fear of open water & lack of control diving presented.

It demands the power to overcome fear, control the body & mind, & to trust your partner.

I truly feel in love with my wife underwater. Her presence while I was getting certified allowed me to slow down, see the world as I never have before, & with the help@of a spear gun -harvest our date night, above a cliff in Mexico, dinner.

If your a family man & God is calling you to embrace your biblical masculinity & get back to the earth, drop "Fearless" 👇 & let's connect on how we can embrace your calling.

What is fear keeping you from achieving? 

#spearfishing #scuba #scubadive #biblicalmasculinity #masculinity #godscalling #fathers #masculine #christianmen #adventureseeker #outdoorsman
